WEBVTT



00:00:09.088 --> 00:00:19.136
So as we continue on our journey in the season of Lent, we're in week four, and we find ourselves in Matthew chapter 19, where Jesus encounters the rich young.

00:00:18.656 --> 00:00:28.608
rich young ruler. He's just moved into the region of Judea. And this man comes up and says, God, what do I need to do to follow you, to give my life to you? And Jesus says, God,

00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:33.088
Obey the commandments that I've given you in the word and do all that I've given you.

00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:41.024
And he says, I've done it. I've done all of these things. And he says, all right, now go sell all of your possessions, give it to the poor and come follow me.

00:00:41.152 --> 00:00:44.096
And the rich young ruler walks away saddened.

00:00:43.904 --> 00:00:50.080
Because he knows he has a lot of stuff, a lot of possessions, and he knows that this is going to be a really hard task for him.

00:00:50.272 --> 00:00:52.224
I think Jesus knew that as well.

00:00:52.128 --> 00:00:56.864
And he knew that there was something that he was holding onto in his heart above him.

00:00:56.480 --> 00:01:06.112
And so as he walks with this man, as he's walking with his disciples, there's this truth that comes out that it's really hard to give things up sometimes.

00:01:05.888 --> 00:01:15.936
And I know that in our comfort, sometimes we forget that it's what God has called us to as followers of Jesus Christ, to give up ourselves, to give up our

00:01:15.456 --> 00:01:20.288
Give up our own desires to give up our own wants for the sake of Jesus Christ.

00:01:20.320 --> 00:01:28.928
In the season of Lent, we often will give up something that reminds us throughout the day to pray, to focus in on Jesus Christ.

00:01:28.864 --> 00:01:38.912
And I don't think that this is a practice just meant to kind of for a season ward off sugar and candy, but this is a season to be reminded that Jesus is the

00:01:38.432 --> 00:01:40.992
Jesus is the most vital thing in our lives.

00:01:40.864 --> 00:01:50.912
that there is nothing in our lives above Jesus Christ. And when we put aside the comforts of everyday life and everyday living, and we say, God, I want to focus my heart

00:01:50.432 --> 00:01:53.440
It's my heart and my mind on you and you alone.

00:01:53.440 --> 00:02:00.512
It's just this great reminder that helps us to stay focused on who God is and what He's called us to do in this life.

00:02:00.544 --> 00:02:08.032
He's called us to make much of him, to give him glory, to worship and glorify him. And so as we...

00:02:07.712 --> 00:02:12.608
go through the season of Lent, we're ultimately looking forward to the day of Easter.

00:02:12.576 --> 00:02:14.656
where Jesus came back.

00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:22.080
after he died and paid the penalty for our sins. this is just a reminder that this life is not just about us.

00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:32.288
This Past Week in Jim's sermon he talked about in matthew chapter 10 what it was to be a disciple going off to the wolves ultimately right and

00:02:31.808 --> 00:02:34.688
And how they would go taking nothing with them.

00:02:34.688 --> 00:02:36.832
Because God was their provision.

00:02:37.088 --> 00:02:39.680
May this season of Lent just be the reminder.

00:02:39.552 --> 00:02:41.632
That God is our provision.

00:02:41.536 --> 00:02:50.016
That day by day, as we look forward to Easter, as we've given these things up for Lent, it's just that reminder that let God be our provision.

00:02:49.888 --> 00:02:59.776
As we might step out into workplaces or school or different scenarios that are really difficult, may it be a reminder that he is the one that we need most in this time.

00:02:59.744 --> 00:03:05.088
And he is the one that will walk beside us and he will shepherd us through that valley.
